      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the overview. i've been reading some stuff online and it feels like some people are saying the school is just trying to be \"progressive\" and that the parents who are worried are just being \"bigoted\" or \"uneducated.\" is there any truth to that? like, is it actually a fact that the curriculum is better for kids, or is that just one way of looking at it?",
